[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rain warning for south and mid Wales prompts fresh flood risk

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A warning has been issued for rain across south and parts of mid Wales over the weekend which could lead to localised flooding.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The Met Office said outbreaks could bring up to 20mm of rain in a relatively short period of time.
It also warned of possible transport disruption.
The warning from 08:00 GMT on Saturday until 12:00 GMT on Sunday is for all of south Wales and Powys.
